               <history>
                  
                  
               <origin>
                     <origDate calendar="gregorian" notAfter="1854">Dated to circa 1850 by Vinson (1868) and to 1850 by Cabaton (1912), on unstated grounds (presumably palaeographical and material analysis arguments).

Internally dated to the year <foreign xml:lang="ta">piramāti</foreign> of the Jovian cycle, that is, CE 1819-1820, 1759-1760, 1699-1700, etc. See colophons (U3, 
<locus facs="550">f248v5</locus> and U4, <locus facs="67">f[1], column 1, line 3</locus>). Vinson mentions the internal in Vinson et al. (1866-). Not dated by Cabaton (1912). Not after 1854, since part of the collection of <persName role="collector">Édouard Ariel</persName> (1818-1854), bequeathed in 1855 to the Société Asiatique, Paris (Rosny 1868).</origDate>
                     <origPlace>South India, Tamilnadu.</origPlace>
                  </origin><provenance><p>Owned by <persName role="collector">Édouard Ariel</persName> (1818-1854). Bequeathed by Édouard Ariel to Société Asiatique (Rosny 1868, p. 177).</p></provenance><acquisition>
                     <p>Received, August 1st, 1866, from the Société Asiatique. See BnF, département des Manuscrits, inventaire 7 = <title>Dons: manuscrits et imprimés documentaires, 1848-1895</title>, no. 1192.</p>
                  </acquisition></history>
